column2:
I have first hand experience of DV and watching her take the stand and doing some poor acting, make me cringe almost as bad as the memories of being foolish enough to let myself be on the receiving end of violent partner.
On the other hand, when Mr.Depp described his experiences, I could relate and sympathise, because not only is he a good professional, he has clearly been unjustly accused of a crime, he did not commit.
What he is doing, is so historically significant, not only is he standing up for himself, but he is giving a voice to countless men, who suffer in silence, because generally it is assumed, that men should just "suck it up"
The fact that she admitted that "adult men don't cry" is cringeworthy and so sexist, I have no words to describe her bias.
I may be the world's worst feminist, but I do insist that all, men and women, should have equal rights and suffer equal consequences.
